1
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:16,533
Raichu, it hurts!

2
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,200
I wanted to go back to him
earlier.

3
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,500
But I stopped myself
from doing so.

4
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,000
She broke up with me.

5
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,867
She's not meant for you.

6
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:24,033
I need to fight for her.

7
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:25,733
I don't want to give up.

8
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,733
Just let her go.

9
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,100
Forget her.

10
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:30,033
Sab, she's the one I love.

11
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,600
I love my mom more than him.

12
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:33,533
And I only have one mom.

13
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,000
If I lose her,
I can't find another one.

14
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,400
I thought you chose them
over me.

15
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,667
I'm sorry about what I said.

16
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,033
Don't worry, Mom.

17
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:45,133
I'm letting Red go.

18
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:48,200
Are you happy now that you broke
up with Red?

19
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,233
You look miserable.

20
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,333
Okay, let's make a deal.

21
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,900
You have to beat your record.

22
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:56,433
If you lose, you have to get
back with Red.

23
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,467
Eden! Eden!

24
00:00:58,533 --> 00:01:00,133
The last thing I remember

25
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,233
is when I was swimming
in the pool.

26
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,333
And then I felt dizzy.

27
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,633
When was your last menstruation?

28
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,400
Are you really one month
delayed?

29
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,533
Yes.

30
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,767
I still don't have my period
up until now.

31
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:14,433
It's almost filled.

32
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:19,433
I'll have enough money
for Yenyen's enrollment.

33
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:23,300
Raichu, I'm pregnant.

34
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,267
I'm pregnant!

35
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,300
Raichu, what am I going to do?

36
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:39,500
Have you already deposited
the money?

37
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,000
I'm going to issue a check
later today.

38
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:44,200
I'm going to buy a new bag.

39
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:45,667
Make sure it won't bounce.

40
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:50,833
Make sure you have it deposited.

41
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,200
Okay, bye.

42
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:56,700
Hi, Mom.

43
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:57,733
Hey.

44
00:02:04,267 --> 00:02:06,000
I think you're right.

45
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,300
I'm right?

46
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:14,333
About what?

47
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:22,267
I agree with your decision
to send me to the US.

48
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:28,100
That's good news!

49
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:29,133
Fantastic!

50
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:34,033
Okay, let me tell your dad.

51
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:36,600
And I'll book your ticket, okay?

52
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,333
Be quiet.

53
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,500
Hush!

54
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,467
Your mom might hear you.

55
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,700
Raichu, what am I going to do?

56
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:57,433
What am I going to do?

57
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:00,933
This could be a false positive,
right?

58
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,633
It could be inaccurate.

59
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:05,533
Maybe we should buy another one.

60
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,467
I hope you're right.

61
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,533
That's the reason we bought
that pregnancy test, remember?

62
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,767
Because you were delayed
and you felt dizzy.

63
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:19,467
What am I going to do?

64
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,700
Just relax.

65
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,200
I'm sure your mom won't kick you
out of the house,

66
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:26,900
especially now
that you're pregnant.

67
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,733
What should I do?

68
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,900
What's going to happen to me?

69
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:38,833
-Eden...
-What am I going to tell my mom?

70
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:39,867
Oh, no!

71
00:03:41,067 --> 00:03:42,967
You broke up with Red already.

72
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:46,033
Who are you going to ask
for help now?

73
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:57,867
Hey.

74
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,900
You made a good decision.

75
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:03,133
You'll have a better future
in the US.

76
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,467
You're used to living there,
anyway.

77
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:06,800
I know.

78
00:04:06,867 --> 00:04:08,800
That's why I let mom know
right away.

79
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,800
Don't worry.

80
00:04:12,867 --> 00:04:14,967
We'll visit you often.

81
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,433
We'll support you all the way.

82
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,900
You're our only child.

83
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:22,500
We'll be right by your side.

84
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:25,833
All done!

85
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,500
I booked your ticket.

86
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,333
Everything is set.

87
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,300
You are leaving in two days.

88
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:35,133
In two days?

89
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,767
Why should we delay it?

90
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:40,433
Your Aunt Claudette
will pick you up

91
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,633
as soon as you arrive.

92
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,867
I've already talked to her.

93
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:48,800
Red needs to know, Eden.

94
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:51,533
You can't keep this from him.

95
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,000
What about my mom?

96
00:04:56,733 --> 00:04:57,767
Your mom?

97
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:02,300
She won't kick you out,

98
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,633
especially now
that you're pregnant.

99
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,533
Yen?

100
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:11,567
Fix yourself.

101
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:13,067
Hurry, get yourself together.

102
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:14,967
- She can't see you like that.
- Mom.

103
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,367
You're taking forever in there.

104
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:17,733
We're coming out.

105
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:26,067
Red, we've been planning
about this.

106
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:29,533
We're just waiting for you
to be ready.

107
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:33,267
And since now that you
already want to go to the US,

108
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,500
everything is set.

109
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,767
We just want you
to have a better life.

110
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:45,233
Thanks, Mom.

111
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:46,867
Thanks, Dad.

112
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:49,167
I think I'll have a better life
there.

113
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:51,533
And...

114
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,133
start fresh. Right?

115
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,667
- New beginnings.
- Yes.

116
00:05:56,367 --> 00:06:00,500
Yenyen was right when she said
we shouldn't hurt our parents.

117
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:04,667
Yes, maybe she's right.

118
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:10,033
Anyway, I think
you should pack your bags.

119
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:12,767
Check your clothes.
If you need anything else,

120
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:16,067
we can buy it now.
So you won't have to rush.

121
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:17,133
Okay.

122
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,233
- Mom.
- Sorry, Auntie.

123
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,400
It's too thick.

124
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:30,733
It took a long time.
I don't know how that happens.

125
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,100
It isn't a business,
but I made it grow.

126
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:35,667
So funny, right?

127
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:40,067
You're always messing around.

128
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,833
Mom, we're just going to go
to my room.

129
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,233
Okay.

130
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,533
- Amanda.
 - Yes?

131
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,233
I got the food.

132
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:04,300
I'm in the bathroom.

133
00:07:05,933 --> 00:07:08,767
What are you doing
with the garbage?

134
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,033
That's dirty.
We're about to eat.

135
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,133
Wash your hands.

136
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,233
I'm not going to eat it.

137
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,733
I'll just take care of this
later.

138
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,600
Let's eat.

139
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:17,700
Okay.

140
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:25,867
Hon, I ordered some cochinillo.

141
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:28,567
It's Red's favorite.
I'm sure he's going to love it.

142
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:30,833
You're so sweet.

143
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,100
Probably that's why
you convinced him

144
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:33,567
to go back to the States.

145
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,600
He has to.

146
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:41,300
Or Eden would have managed
to seduce him.

147
00:07:41,367 --> 00:07:42,567
Such a social climber!

148
00:07:44,733 --> 00:07:47,567
Red is a prize catch.

149
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,967
That's why she's aiming for him.

150
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:51,900
Let it go.

151
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:54,867
It's useless for us
to talk about them.

152
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,200
Red is about to move on.

153
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:59,100
And in time,
he will forget about Eden.

154
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:11,500
Yenyen.

155
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:15,600
Why aren't you touching
your food?

156
00:08:16,667 --> 00:08:18,600
I don't feel like eating.

157
00:08:18,667 --> 00:08:20,633
Don't you like the food?

158
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,500
Your aunt told me
it's your favorite.

159
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,933
Right! It's fried chicken.

160
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:29,867
I'm not hungry.

161
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,833
And I feel tired.

162
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,367
I'm going to get some rest.

163
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,233
Unbelievable.

164
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,567
Yenyen loves to eat.

165
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:52,900
And this is her favorite.

166
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,767
I'm not used to seeing her
like that.

167
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,067
I'm taking her drumstick, then.

168
00:08:59,667 --> 00:09:00,833
Hi!

169
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:02,567
- Hello, Uncle.
- Hi.

170
00:09:03,767 --> 00:09:05,000
Hello, Uncle Victor.

171
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:07,067
Hello, Aunt Rina.

172
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:08,067
Hi.
Hi.

173
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:11,433
Are you hungry?

174
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,533
You want something to eat?

175
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,133
- Oh, no thank you.
- No, are you sure?

176
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,733
- Yes.
- Thank you very much

177
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,467
for coming here
at such short notice.

178
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:23,000
Hon, I invited Sabina
to join us for dinner.

179
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:26,967
Let's have a farewell party
for Red.

180
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,667
Good idea.

181
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:30,567
That way, you'll have more time
to hang out with Red

182
00:09:30,633 --> 00:09:32,167
before he leaves.

183
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:34,000
When is he leaving?

184
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:35,667
In two days.

185
00:09:35,733 --> 00:09:37,633
Oh, you'll still have time
to catch up.

186
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,800
He's upstairs.
Why don't you go up?

187
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,833
- Okay. I'm going to go up.
- Okay.

188
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:48,967
No more headache for me.

189
00:09:55,433 --> 00:09:57,267
Hon...

190
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,100
thank you. Thank you so much
for your understanding.

191
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,267
No worries, Hon.

192
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:06,300
As long as you don't get
yourself in any trouble,

193
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,767
you won't be having
any problems.

194
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,967
Eden, are you not feeling well?

195
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:41,733
I'll take you to the clinic.

196
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,733
No, Mom. I'm fine.

197
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:45,933
Did I scare you?

198
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:54,200
I'm fine, Mom.

199
00:10:54,267 --> 00:10:56,267
I'm not sick.

200
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:59,633
It's better to get you checked.

201
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,833
No, Mom. It will only cost us
money.

202
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:04,267
I feel fine.

203
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:06,467
Eden, let's go to the clinic.

204
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:07,600
Let's get you checked up,

205
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,500
so we can find out
why you don't feel like eating.

206
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:12,567
We never know.
You might be sick.

207
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:15,367
We don't want it to get worse.

208
00:11:16,567 --> 00:11:17,700
No, Mom.

209
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:21,600
I just don't feel like eating.

210
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:23,700
I'm fine, Mom.
Let's not have extra expenses.

211
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,567
- Are you sure?
- Yes, Mom.

212
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,267
Okay.

213
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:35,433
I'll sleep here with you.

214
00:11:39,467 --> 00:11:42,067
I'm staying here
with my good daughter.

215
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:55,000
So is Yenyen the reason
you're leaving?

216
00:11:58,167 --> 00:12:00,767
I just want a new environment.

217
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:02,900
After the plane crash,

218
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:06,167
I just wanted to forget
the trauma.

219
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:08,000
Good for you.

220
00:12:08,067 --> 00:12:10,400
Actually, my parents
are planning the same thing

221
00:12:10,467 --> 00:12:11,633
for me.

222
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,133
You're going to the US too?

223
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,167
Yes.

224
00:12:15,567 --> 00:12:16,533
Why?

225
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,933
Don't worry.

226
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:22,267
I'm not going to push myself
on you.

227
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,567
In fact,
we can still be friends.

228
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,600
Right?

229
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,433
Of course.

230
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,467
Awesome!

231
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,333
Is this what you've been hiding
from me?

232
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,633
Yes.

233
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,133
I made this for you.

234
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,233
This one's mine.
I'm wearing it already.

235
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,600
I made this for you...

236
00:13:07,467 --> 00:13:09,900
to remind ourselves...

237
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,867
that we'll stay together
forever.

238
00:13:20,433 --> 00:13:24,300
The trees are witness
to my promise,

239
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:27,200
the plants,

240
00:13:27,267 --> 00:13:28,633
the sea,

241
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:29,767
the rain.

242
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:34,967
I hope that these seashells
will bind us together...

243
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:37,933
forever.

244
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,300
Come on, mom and dad
are waiting for us.

245
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:14,067
Okay, wait. Wait for me.

246
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,333
It must be nice
to have children.

247
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:22,833
Once we have a child,
I'll be a hands-on dad.

248
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:27,100
That's what I want
for my future child too.

249
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:30,233
You know how I grew up
without a dad.

250
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,267
And your mom raised you
on her own.

251
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,900
That's right.

252
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:36,133
I hope my child

253
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,700
won't have to experience
growing up without a dad.

254
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,433
Don't worry, Yen.

255
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:47,633
Our child will grow up with me
at his side.

256
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,500
I promise.

257
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:50,967
- Really?
- Yes.

258
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,900
Sweetie...

259
00:15:05,367 --> 00:15:06,800
I'm sorry.

260
00:15:08,433 --> 00:15:10,033
I don't know what to do.

261
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:15,033
I don't want you to grow up
without a father.

262
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:20,100
I don't want you to experience
everything I've been through.

263
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:29,033
Your father should know
that you exist.

264
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,633
I can't keep you from him.

265
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,233
I don't want to be unfair
to both of you.

266
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,200
It's hard,

267
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:41,267
but I have to do what's right.

268
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,767
Wait! Wait!

269
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:03,067
Why do you have
Red's belongings?

270
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:05,167
He asked me to get it for him.

271
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:06,233
What?

272
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,267
Why? What's going on?

273
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:11,033
Didn't you and Eden know?

274
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:13,000
He's leaving for the US today.

275
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:14,867
He'll be staying there for good.

276
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,733
Liar. You're making up stories.

277
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,233
He didn't say anything
about that.

278
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,933
Why would he need to tell you?

279
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,933
It's the least of his concern.

280
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,467
Okay? Bye!

281
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:25,533
Okay?

282
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,567
Bye!

283
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,067
Raichu.

284
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:35,267
Eden! I'm glad you're here.

285
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:36,367
I have to tell you something.
Come on!

286
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:37,700
Let me talk first.

287
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:39,633
I'm going to meet with Red.

288
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,067
I'm going to tell him
I'm pregnant.

289
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:45,000
I'm ready to face his parents.

290
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:47,067
We'll tell them the truth
together.

291
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:48,767
That's the right thing to do,
right?

292
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:52,433
That's if you get to him
on time.

293
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,667
What?

294
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:55,633
Eden, he's leaving!

295
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,333
Today is his flight to the US!

296
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,667
He's going to stay there
for good!

297
00:16:58,733 --> 00:16:59,433
What?

298
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,700
He's not picking up his phone!

299
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:10,000
Why don't we go to him?

300
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:11,500
Come on! Let's go!

301
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,133
He looks like you.

302
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,433
Look at his eyes.

303
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:22,167
Is that your baby?

304
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:24,333
- Yes, Sir.
- Yes, Sir.

305
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,633
He's so cute! Congrats!

306
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,733
Thank you.

307
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,500
We want you to be his godfather,
Sir.

308
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:29,633
Yes, sure.

309
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:31,700
- When I get back.
- Thank you.

310
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:35,133
What's his name?

311
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,333
Red, we have to go.

312
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,133
Come on, your parents
will follow us to the airport.

313
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,267
- Bye. See you soon.
- Bye, take care.

314
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:01,433
I hope he's still here.

315
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:04,767
We have to hurry, Raichu.
He needs to know I'm pregnant.

316
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:06,200
I'm tired.

317
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:15,667
Is that Red?

318
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,300
It's him!

319
00:18:18,367 --> 00:18:19,867
- Eden!
- Red!

320
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:24,600
Red! Red!

321
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:34,667
Is it Red?

322
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:35,867
- Red!
- Yen!

323
00:18:37,967 --> 00:18:39,600
Red, I need to tell you
something.

324
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:47,267
I know you're going
to the States.

325
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,567
I don't want to stop you
from leaving, but...

326
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:51,867
But you need to know
I'm pregnant.

327
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:55,933
You have a right to this child
too.

328
00:18:58,133 --> 00:18:59,433
I'm going to be a father?

329
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:04,967
I love you so much, Yen,
but I didn't expect this.

330
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:07,900
Even I can't believe
what is happening.

331
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:10,367
I'm scared. I don't know
what I should do.

332
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,467
I can't leave you.

333
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,267
I can't leave you
in this situation.

334
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,867
What are we going to do?

335
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:22,867
I don't know. All I know
is I'll never leave you, Yen.

336
00:19:25,667 --> 00:19:27,000
That's enough.

337
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,200
Red, let's go.

338
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:30,967
You'll miss your flight.

339
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:35,667
I'm not going to the airport.

340
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:38,200
Just give me the car keys.

341
00:19:38,267 --> 00:19:39,467
What are you talking about?

342
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,933
Do you want your mom
to chew me up?

343
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,067
Leave that woman!

344
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:46,233
And you, why did you come here?

345
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,267
What did you tell him?

346
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:49,300
Uncle! Don't talk to her
like that,

347
00:19:49,367 --> 00:19:50,733
or you'll have to deal with me.

348
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:53,300
Are you serious?

349
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:55,167
Do you want me to smack you
on the head?

350
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,567
Let's go, come with me!

351
00:19:58,067 --> 00:19:59,767
Red!

352
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:00,900
Come on, get in the car!

353
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:01,967
- Let's go!
- Raichu!

354
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:04,400
- Let's go.
- Red!

355
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:06,167
Come on, Yen.

356
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:07,200
Red!

357
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,900
Hon, I'm right outside.

358
00:20:22,967 --> 00:20:24,400
I'll just see you out here.

359
00:20:24,467 --> 00:20:25,433
Okay.

360
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:30,933
The hell!

361
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:39,733
Why are you walking back here?

362
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,700
Where's Red?

363
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:44,800
Did your car break down?

364
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,333
For God's sake, Zandro!

365
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,933
Say something!

366
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,767
Answer me!

367
00:20:55,433 --> 00:20:58,833
Red left with Eden.

368
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,700
- I think they eloped.
- What?

369
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,867
Why did you let him go with her?

370
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,133
Didn't I tell you
to keep an eye on him?

371
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,467
And what did you do?

372
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:12,433
You just let them elope!

373
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,500
What's gotten into you, Zandro!

374
00:21:14,567 --> 00:21:16,200
You're so stupid!

375
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:17,467
Rina, stop it.

376
00:21:17,533 --> 00:21:18,533
What's going on?

377
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,000
This stupid Zandro!

378
00:21:21,067 --> 00:21:22,267
He let our son go!

379
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:25,067
He eloped with Eden!

380
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:27,733
Our son is gone, Victor!

381
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,500
He left us!

382
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:30,667
Stupid!

383
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,667
Eden, you can drop me off here.

384
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:38,867
I'll just take a taxi.

385
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:40,367
- So you two can talk.
- Are you sure?

386
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:41,400
- Are you sure, Raichu?
- Yes.

387
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,000
Take care, okay?

388
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:44,300
- Be safe.
- I will.

389
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:45,333
Be safe, too.

390
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,700
Red, where are we going?

391
00:22:01,667 --> 00:22:03,200
I don't know.

392
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:04,300
We'll go wherever.

393
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:07,567
We just need to get away
from here.

394
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:10,333
Let's think of a plan later.

395
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,067
I'm scared.

396
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:14,900
I know. We're in
a difficult situation, Yen.

397
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,567
I'm sorry.

398
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:18,700
No, don't be, okay?

399
00:22:18,767 --> 00:22:20,167
We both wanted this.

400
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:24,900
Let's just think of a plan.

401
00:22:24,967 --> 00:22:26,267
Let's think
about where we should go.

402
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:33,300
Luckily, you used my car.

403
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:36,600
It has GPS, so we can track
where they went.

404
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:38,133
What if we lose signal?

405
00:22:39,167 --> 00:22:40,267
Then we'll have a problem.

406
00:22:40,333 --> 00:22:42,333
And this is all your fault,
Zandro!

407
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:43,900
I told you to take care
of my son!

408
00:22:43,967 --> 00:22:46,367
What did you do?
You gave him a car,

409
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:49,000
so he can elope with Eden!

410
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:51,800
Your son punched and kicked me,
Rina!

411
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:53,900
I didn't fight him back
because I felt sorry for him!

412
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,033
You felt sorry for him?

413
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:58,300
Zandro!

414
00:22:58,367 --> 00:23:00,533
You should feel bad for me!
I just lost my son!

415
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,967
You let him elope with Eden!

416
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:07,300
You know how much I hate her!

417
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:08,700
She is Amanda's daughter!

418
00:23:08,767 --> 00:23:10,500
Rina, will you shut up?

419
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:12,667
You're making my ears hurt!

420
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:13,933
I want our son back!

421
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,733
Victor, find him!

422
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:20,300
Here, there's a signal.

423
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:22,300
- The GPS is working.
- Where is he?

424
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:24,633
He's here.

425
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,500
We lost the signal.

426
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,267
Stop touching it!

427
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:32,600
You keep butting in!

428
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:13,900
Hello, Eden?

429
00:24:13,967 --> 00:24:14,933
Eden?

430
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:18,267
- Eden? Hello?
- Where is my daughter?

431
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:19,700
Where is she?

432
00:24:19,767 --> 00:24:21,500
Please, tell me.

433
00:24:21,567 --> 00:24:23,400
Raichu, don't lie to us.

434
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:25,567
Where is Eden? Where did she go?

435
00:24:25,633 --> 00:24:27,533
Can you please drive faster,
Zandro?

436
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,167
You're so slow! Hurry up!

437
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:31,667
We might get in an accident
if I drive faster.

438
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:32,867
Can you stop, Rina!

439
00:24:32,933 --> 00:24:34,667
It already happened. We can't do
anything about it now.

440
00:24:34,733 --> 00:24:36,900
I don't want Red to get married.

441
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:40,533
And I don't want Eden
to become my daughter-in-law.

442
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,433
Why don't you just talk
with them?

443
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:44,333
- You guys are their parents.
- I don't want Rina

444
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,467
to become my in-law. No way!

445
00:24:45,533 --> 00:24:48,733
I will do anything
to get Eden back.

446
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,767
How are you, Eden?

447
00:24:50,833 --> 00:24:52,267
Did you really think
you could run away from us?

448
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:53,700
Opportunist!

449
00:24:53,767 --> 00:24:55,167
I will destroy your face!

450
00:24:55,233 --> 00:24:56,567
Let's see if my son
will still like you...

451
00:24:56,633 --> 00:24:57,867
- Mom!
- after this!

452
00:24:57,933 --> 00:24:59,400
You can't hurt her!
